==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: enterics
<hw>enterics</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>rod-shaped gram-negative bacteria
of the family <fam>Enterobacteriaceae</fam>; most occur normally or
pathogenically in intestines of humans and other animals; those of the
genus <gen>Erwinia</gen> are found in plants.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> enteric bacteria, enterobacteria.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

